_Hif’il_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_hif’il_ past tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                              | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | הִבְדַּלְתִּי<br>_hivdalti_<br>I separated | \<       | הִבְדַּלְנוּ<br>_hivdalnu_<br>We seperated | \< |
| *Second-Person* | הִבְדַּלְתָּ <br>_hivdaltau_<br> You [male] separated | הִבְדַּלְתְּ <br>_hivdalt_<br> You [female] separated  | הִבְדַּלְתֶּם <br>_hivdaltem_<br> You [males] separated  | הִבְדַּלְתֶּן <br>_hivdalten_<br> You [females] separated |
| *Third-Person* | הִבְדִּיל <br>_hivdil_<br> He separated | הִבְדִּילָה <br>_hivdilau_<br> She separated  | הִבְדִּילוּ <br>_hivdilu_<br> They [male or female] separated  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ב, ‎ד, and ל above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
